      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 mt-6">Framer: Design-Focused Practices</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Created a beautiful, modern medical site with excellent visuals. Best for specialists where aesthetics matter (cosmetic surgery, dermatology, dental).
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <strong>Best for:</strong> Cosmetic specialists, dental practices, any practice where image matters.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">HIPAA Considerations</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <strong>Important:</strong> AI website builders themselves are not HIPAA-compliant by default. For true HIPAA compliance, you need:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>BAA (Business Associate Agreement) with your hosting provider</li>
        <li>Encrypted data transmission (SSL)</li>
        <li>Secure appointment booking systems</li>
        <li>Patient data stored in HIPAA-compliant systems</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
        Most AI builders (including Durable, Framer, Wix) can host the front-end of your medical site. But for actual patient data (appointments, records), use specialized healthcare software.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">Both have free trials. Test with your medical practice information.</p>
